# ALTERNATIVE NAME 4: Statement 4 - While plastic pollution is a major concern that affects many aspects of our daily lives, we should be wary of banning non-biodegradable plastics in a blanket way. We should instead focus on the disposal of non-biodegradable plastics, making it more expensive for people to throw these plastics into the environment, and also to encourage people to recycle these plastics. We should also look at producing goods that use non-biodegradable plastics in ways that allow for easier recycling and re-use, rather than a single use.
